Job Description
QUALIFICATIONS, KNOWLEDGE AND SKILL REQUIREMENTS:
The qualifications and skill requirements for this position include
Must have a minimum of a 2.5 GPA and be currently enrolled in a post-secondary institution and in good standing with the college;
Ability to supervise and advise students participating in the IRSC Education Talent Search program;
Possess excellent verbal and written communication skills in order to communicate effectively with students, parents, Educational Talent Search personnel, and the public;
Possess reasoning skills and be relied upon to utilize good judgement on issues relating to health and safety;
Two (2) letters of recommendation from at least two (2) faculty or staff members;
Must have demonstrated ability in working with a diverse group of students.
The following is preferred:
45 college credit hours completed;
Previous experience working with disadvantaged and underrepresented student populations;
ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
The essential job functions and responsibilities for this position include, but are not limited to:
Creating a community environment conducive to the academic enhancement, personal growth, and development of Educational Talent Search students;
Assist with program fieldtrips and functions;
Assist students and parents in completing test registrations, college admissions applications, and the FASFA (Federal Application for Student Financial Aid) forms;
Provide tutoring support for middle and high school students in math, English, or other school subjects;
Assist with collection of program data for monitoring and evaluation purposes;
Working with middle and high school students to help them understand key concepts, especially those learned in the classroom;
Assist students with homework and/or study skills.
SPECIFIC DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
The specific duties and responsibilities for this position include, but are not limited to
Flexible work hours;
Occasionally supervising students in the evening hours to ensure general safety and compliance of program rules;
Supervising students at recreational activities, field trips, and cultural trips;
Providing assistance with daytime and evening programs as needed;
Acting as a referral agent in acquiring students with all facilities and services on the campus;
Remaining sensitive to subtle mood changes and erratic behavior that may be exhibited by the students;
Supervising students’ daily schedule of activities;
Assisting in the process of identifying student needs and interests;
Assisting in coordinating and providing oversight of students during planned ETS activities;
Assisting with check-in registration and check-out procedures;
Helping to maintain an efficient and effective operation;
Assisting with physical training/team sports/leisure activities, etc.;
Handling minor problems and referring all others to the appropriate ETS staff;
Monitoring students during classes;
Assisting other program staff as needed;
Completing other duties and responsibilities that are with the scope of the program and assigned by the Program Director, Academic Coordinators, and Program Assistant.
PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS:
This position requires an ability to sit, stand, walk, bend, lift, reach up, stoop, and carry items occasionally in excess of twenty-five (25) pounds. It also requires manual dexterity to operate standard office machines, such as, copier, fax, calculator, telephone, and other equipment as necessary. IRSC expects its employees to follow proper safety standards while employed by the College.
Classification
Student Workers
Supervisory
No
FLSA Exempt
No
Employment Type
Temporary (Fixed Term)
Compensation and Application Deadline
Commensurate with Degree/Experience Level | Adjunct positions at IRSC are filled on an as needed basis and are permanently posted. You will be contacted for an interview only if the related department has positions to fill.
